John Wagner (wag5@kimbark.uchicago.edu) wrote:
: Has anyone considered planting a small thermal explosive inside the
: hard drive triggerable by being lifted from its surface, unless a
: concealed switch is activated to stop the explosion for purposes of user
: manipulation?
: 			John
:
The trouble with an active method of opponent thwarting is that by
not informing the authorities as soon as possible about the explosive
you would at the very least be guilty of obstruction of justice, a serious
crime that may net you more jail time than whatever is indicated on the
search warrant.

The ubiquitous ram disk continues to be a far-and-away favorite among
people wishing to deny data to opponents that can capture their
equipment at random times.  As far as I know, no opponent brings
a UPS with them on raids (yet).

 	
